# GajiGuard вҖ” MVP Spec & Implementation Plan

**Malaysian B2C Subscription & BNPL Manager**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a comprehensive spec covering all 8 deliverables. Review each section and flag anything you want changed before we start building.

---

## 1. Product Requirements Document (PRD)

### 1.1 Target User

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Demographics** | Malaysians aged 20вҖ“40, middle/low income (RM 2,000вҖ“6,000/month) |
| **Behavior** | Uses 2вҖ“8 digital subscriptions (Spotify, Netflix, iQIYI, Disney+) and 1вҖ“5 active BNPL plans (Grab PayLater, Atome, SPayLater, hoolah) |
| **Pain point** | Loses track of when payments are due, surprised by deductions, doesn't know total monthly commitments |
| **Tech comfort** | Comfortable with smartphone/web apps, uses e-wallets, but not spreadsheet power users |
| **Language** | English-first UI with Malay-friendly copy (e.g., "Langganan", "Ansuran") |

### 1.2 Core User Journeys

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Land on homepage] --> B[Sign up / Login]
    B --> C[Empty calendar вҶ’ prompted to add first item]
    C --> D[Quick-add subscription or BNPL]
    D --> E[See items on calendar]
    E --> F[View day details вҶ’ mark as paid]
    E --> G[See upcoming sidebar вҶ’ total RM this month]
    G --> H{Hit 3-item limit?}
    H -->|Yes| I[Upgrade prompt вҶ’ Polar checkout вҶ’ RM10/month]
    H -->|No| D
    I --> J[Unlimited items]
```

**Journey 1: First-time user adds a subscription**
1. Sign up with email/password (or Google)
2. Empty state shows "Add your first subscription" CTA
3. Opens quick-add sheet вҶ’ types "Netflix", RM55/month, billing day 15
4. Calendar populates with Netflix marker on the 15th
5. Upcoming sidebar shows "Netflix вҖ” RM55 вҖ” due in 8 days"

**Journey 2: User adds a BNPL installment**
1. Quick-add вҶ’ selects "BNPL/Installment" tab
2. Enters: "iPhone 16 via Atome", RM150/month, 6 installments, started Jan 2025
3. Calendar shows markers on upcoming due dates; completed installments greyed out
4. Progress badge shows "3/6 paid"

**Journey 3: User hits free limit вҶ’ upgrades**
1. Tries to add 4th item вҶ’ dialog with upgrade prompt
2. Clicks "Upgrade to Pro вҖ” RM10/month"
3. Polar checkout overlay вҶ’ completes payment
4. Webhook fires вҶ’ entitlement updated вҶ’ can now add unlimited items

**Journey 4: Mark as paid**
1. Taps a due date on calendar вҶ’ day drawer opens
2. Sees "Netflix вҖ” RM55 вҖ” Due today"
3. Taps "Mark as Paid" вҶ’ occurrence marked, next due date calculated
4. Toast: "Nice! Netflix marked as paid вң“"

